dct_title_s: Austria 1:7,500. Town Plan of Modling. G.S.G.S. no. 4483
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no.4483. [Italy]. Survey Directorate. Allied Forces Headquarters. Alternate title: Town plan of Modling. Also designated as A.F. 5922.Relief shown by 10 metres contour intervals and spot heights. Inset: "Vicinity map." In lower left margin: "Complied from aerial photographs and Austrian maps." In lower right margin: "Drawn and reproduced by 516 Field Survey Coy., R. E. Mar. 1945. With glossary of terms, principal buildings and public places listed and located. Sources: G.S.G.S. 4346, 1:250,000 sheet O49; G.S.G.S. 4416 1:100,000 wheeet X.10; Austria 1:25,000 sheet C5 (1910); Hozel Strassen Karten; Air photographs dated Feb., Aug., Nov., 1944; Autostrassenkarten, Freytag- und Berndt; I.S.T.D. reports 1944. "This town falls on G.S.G.S. 4416 series. Middle Danube 1:100.000, sheet X-10.
